   <head>[Epigram]</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">ADAM alone cou'd not be easy,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">So he must have a wife, an't please ye:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But how did he procure his wife,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To cheer his solitary life?</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why, from a rib ta'en out his side</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Was form'd this necessary bride.</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But how did he the pain beguile?</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Pho! he slept sweetly all the while.</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But when this rib was re-applied,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In woman's form, to Adam's side,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">How then, I pray you, did it answer?</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">He never slept so sweet again, Sir.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
